{
  "metadata": {
    "type": "targeted_grid",
    "name": "hashrate_2016_verification",
    "description": "Verify that hashrate_split non-causality holds at 2016-block retarget conditions.\nAt 144-block retarget (targeted_sweep2_hashrate_economic, 42 scenarios), hashrate_split was shown to have only weak influence on fork outcome when pool_committed_split is fixed above the Foundry flip-point (~0.214). Economic split dominated regardless of hashrate. However, that finding was validated only at 144-block retarget.\nThe 2016-block regime is qualitatively different: the minority chain suffers a much longer difficulty penalty period (~67 min per retarget vs ~5 min), which could amplify the hashrate signal. Specifically, a larger hashrate advantage on v26 means a more severe minority-chain fee squeeze over a much longer window before the retarget cascade fires. This sweep tests whether hashrate_split changes the decision boundary at 2016-block or remains non-causal, as assumed in the Phase 2 PRIM analysis.\nDESIGN (mirrors targeted_sweep2 at 2016-block):\n  - pool_committed_split fixed at 0.50 (above Foundry flip-point; no inversion contamination)\n  - economic_split sampled at 3 levels spanning the transition zone (0.50, 0.60, 0.70)\n  - hashrate_split swept across 6 levels (0.15 \u2192 heavy v26 advantage, 0.65 \u2192 near parity)\n  - Grid: 6 hashrate \u00d7 3 economic = 18 scenarios\n\nEXPECTED OUTCOME (if non-causality holds):\n  - Each economic_split level should produce the same outcome across all hashrate values\n  - econ=0.50: all v26_dominant (0 nodes on v27 via quantization at econ<0.30... wait,\n    actually econ=0.50 \u2192 1 node \u2192 v27_dominant; econ<0.30 \u2192 0 nodes \u2192 v26_dominant)\n  - econ=0.50, 0.60, 0.70: all 1-node configurations \u2192 v27_dominant regardless of hashrate\n  - If hashrate_split IS causal: some hashrate values will flip outcome within an econ row\n\nVALIDATED PARAMS: Uses corrected econ switching parameters (threshold=0.10, inertia=0.05) matching all v2 sweeps. Fixed params from phase 2 medians.\nRUNTIME: 18 scenarios \u00d7 ~13,000s = ~234,000s total (sequential). On lite network at ~60 min/scenario: ~18h. Consider running in 2 parallel namespaces to halve wall time.\nRun command (single namespace):\n  python tools/sweep/1_generate_targeted.py --spec specs/hashrate_2016_verification.yaml\n  python tools/sweep/2_build_configs.py \\\n    --input hashrate_2016_verification/scenarios.json \\\n    --output-dir hashrate_2016_verification\n  python tools/sweep/3_run_sweep.py \\\n    --input hashrate_2016_verification/build_manifest.json \\\n    --results-dir hashrate_2016_verification/results \\\n    --duration 13000 --retarget-interval 2016 --interval 2\n",
    "spec_file": "tools/sweep/specs/hashrate_2016_verification.yaml",
